President Trump recently signed the VA Accountability and Whistleblower Protection Act, which aims to make it easier to suspend or fire government workers, specifically those at national Veterans Affairs offices. The act also speeds up disciplinary appeals, allows for the recoupment of bonuses, and holds more government employees accountable for helping veterans. The president highlighted the importance of protecting veterans, citing instances of mistreatment and neglect in the past. The editorial emphasizes the need to prioritize the well-being of veterans and the ability to remove employees who do not provide proper treatment without going through complex union rules.